article.headline: SE Missouri State 61, Murray State 58
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Terrick Willoughby scored 19 points and Reggie Golson added 15 points and 11 rebounds Saturday night to lead Southeast Missouri to a 61-58 win over Murray State. Dainmon Gonner added 12 points and 10 rebounds for the Redhawks (11-10, 6-4 Ohio Valley Conference), who outrebounded Murray State 33-28. Keith Jenifer scored 15 to lead Murray State (12-8, 7-3), which went only 4 of 14 from 3-point range (29 percent). Golson sank a free throw with 6.5 seconds left to put the Redhawks up 61-58. The Racers had a chance to tie the game, but Jenifer traveled after getting a rebound. Murray State lost despite committing only eight turnovers and shooting 47 percent from the field (26 of 55).
